<p>As shown in 
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="nanomaterials-09-00978-f006">Figure 6</xref>, the internal energy (
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm115">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>E</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mi>P</mi>
       <mi>F</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>) derived from the PF was in excellent agreement with that (
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm116">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>E</mi>
      <mrow>
       <mi>M</mi>
       <mi>D</mi>
      </mrow>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>) obtained by the MD simulations with a relative standard deviation of 0.008%, which is too small to be shown in 
 <xref ref-type="fig" rid="nanomaterials-09-00978-f006">Figure 6</xref>. For temperatures lower than 500 K, the relative error (
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm117">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <mfrac>
      <mrow>
       <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mrow>
         <mi>P</mi>
         <mi>F</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo>−</mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mrow>
         <mi>M</mi>
         <mi>D</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
      </mrow>
      <mrow>
       <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
       <msub>
        <mi>E</mi>
        <mrow>
         <mi>M</mi>
         <mi>D</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msub>
       <mo stretchy="false">|</mo>
      </mrow>
     </mfrac>
     <mo>×</mo>
     <mn>100</mn>
     <mo>%</mo>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula>) was only 0.001% and gradually increased up to 0.021% for 1300 K. It may be expected that the relative error would get smaller if the effective length 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm118">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>L</mi>
      <mi>i</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> of the edge atoms was calculated, instead of replacing 
 <inline-formula>
  <math id="mm119">
   <mrow>
    <mrow>
     <msub>
      <mi>L</mi>
      <mi>i</mi>
     </msub>
    </mrow>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </inline-formula> with the one of the center atom, to calculate Q by Equation (11). 
</p>
